tt+|sv|sjö|c}} {{qualifier|in some cases, not generally}}\n* Tabasaran: {{tt|tab|гьюл}}\n* Tagalog: {{tt+|tl|dagat}}\n* Tahitian: {{t|ty|miti}} {{qualifier|nearshore}}, {{t|ty|tai}} {{qualifier|offing}}, {{t|ty|moana}} {{qualifier|beyond}}\n* Tai Dam: {{tt|blt|ꪙꪾ꫁ꪹꪚꪸ꫁}}\n* Tajik: {{tt+|tg|баҳр}}, {{tt+|tg|дарё}}\n* Talysh:\n*: Asalemi: {{tt|tly|دریا|tr=daryâ}}\n* Tamil: {{tt+|ta|கடல்}}, {{t+|ta|ஆழி}}\n* Tarifit: {{t|rif|rebḥar|m}}\n* Tashelhit: {{t|shi|ilel}}, {{t|shi|lbḥṛ}}\n* Tatar: {{tt+|tt|диңгез}}\n* Tausug: {{tt|tsg|dagat}}\n* Tày: {{tt|tyz|pé}}\n* Telugu: {{tt+|te|సముద్రం}}, {{tt+|te|కడలి}}\n* Ternate: {{t|tft|dai}}\n* Tetum: {{tt|tet|tasi}}\n* Thai: {{tt+|th|ทะเล}}, {{tt+|th|ห้วงน้ำ}}, {{tt+|th|สมุทฺท}}\n* Tibetan: {{tt|bo|བརྐོས}}, {{tt|bo|རྒྱ་མཚོ}}, {{tt|bo|མཚོ}}\n* Tigrinya: {{tt|ti|ባሕሪ}}\n* Tocharian A: {{tt|xto|sāmudtär}}\n* Tocharian B: {{tt|txb|samudtär}}, {{tt|txb|lyam|m}}\n* Tok Pisin: {{tt|tpi|solwara}}, {{tt+|tpi|wara}}, {{tt|tpi|raunwara}}\n* Tongan: {{t|to|tahi}}, {{t|to|vaha}}, {{t|to|moana}}\n* Tupinambá: {{tt|tpn|paranã}}, {{tt|tpn|paranaã}}, {{tt|tpn|paraná}}\n* Turkish: {{tt+|tr|deniz}}, {{tt+|tr|derya}} {{qualifier|large}}\n*: Old Anatolian Turkish: {{t|trk-oat|دَكِزْ|tr=däŋiz}}\n*: Ottoman Turkish: {{tt|ota|دڭز|tr=deñiz}}\n* Turkmen: {{tt|tk|deňiz}}\n* Udihe: {{tt|ude|наму|tr=namu}}\n* Udmurt: {{tt|udm|море}}, {{t|udm|зарезь}}\n* Ukrainian: {{tt+|uk|мо́ре|n}}\n* Unami: {{t|unm|kitahikàn}}\n* Urdu: {{tt|ur|سَمَنْدَر|m|tr=samandar}}, {{t|ur|سَمُنْدَر|tr=samundar}}, {{tt+|ur|بَحْر|m|tr=bahr}}\n* Urum: {{tt|uum|дэниз|tr=déniz}}\n* Uyghur: {{tt|ug|دېڭىز}}\n* Uzbek: {{tt+|uz|dengiz}}\n* Venetan: {{tt+|vec|mar|m}}, {{tt+|vec|mare}}\n* Veps: {{tt|vep|meri}}\n* Vietnamese: {{tt+|vi|biển}}, {{tt+|vi|bể}}\n* Vilamovian: {{tt|wym|mjer}}\n* Volapük: {{tt+|vo|mel}}\n* Vurës: {{tt|msn|naw}}\n* Walloon: {{t-needed|wa}}\n* Welsh: {{tt+|cy|môr}}, {{tt|cy|gweilgi}}\n* Woiwurrung: {{t|wyi|ballim-be warreen}}\n* Wolof: {{tt|wo|gaych}}\n* Xhosa: {{tt|xh|ulwandle}}\n* Yaghnobi: {{t|yai|bahr}}\n* Yakut: {{tt|sah|байҕал}}, {{tt|sah|муора}}\n* Yámana: {{tt|yag|ixa}}\n* Yiddish: {{tt|yi|ים|m|tr=yam}}, {{tt|yi|יאַם|m}}\n* Yoruba: {{tt|yo|òkun|id=sea}}\n* Yup'ik: {{tt|esu|imarpik}}\n* Zazaki: {{tt+|zza|derya}}, {{tt+|zza|dengız}}\n* Zealandic: {{tt|zea|zeê|f}}\n* Zhuang: {{tt|za|haij}}\n* Zulu: {{tt+|zu|ulwandle|c11|c10}}\n}}<!-- close {{multitrans}} -->\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n====See also====\n* {{l|en|ocean}}\n\n===See also===\n*{{l|en|Sea-Tac}}\n\n===References===\n<references/>\n\n===Further reading===\n* {{pedia}}\n* {{R:Webster 1913}}\n* {{R:Century 1911}}\n\n===Anagrams===\n* {{anagrams|en|a=aes|-ase|AES|ASE|EAS|EAs|ESA|Esa|SAE|a**es|aes|ase|eas|esa}}\n\n{{C|en|Bodies of water|Landforms|Seas}}\n\n==Cimbrian==\n\n===Etymology===\nFrom {{inh|cim|gmh|sē}}, from {{inh|cim|goh|sēo}}, from {{inh|cim|gmw-pro|*saiwi}}, from {{inh|cim|gem-pro|*saiwiz||sea, ocean}}. Cognate with {{cog|de|See}}, {{cog|en|sea}}.\n\n===Noun===\n{{cim-noun|m}}\n\n# {{lb|cim|Luserna}} [[lake]]\n\n===References===\n* {{R:Patuzzi}}\n\n{{c|cim|Landforms|Water}}\n\n==Estonian==\n{{attention|et}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{head|et|noun form}}\n\n# {{noun form of|et|siga||gen|s}}\n\n==Garo==\n\n===Verb===\n{{head|grt|verb}}\n\n# to [[write]]\n\n====Derived terms====\n* {{l|grt|segipa}}\n\n==Irish==\n\n===Alternative forms===\n* {{alter|ga|seadh||superseded}}\n\n===Etymology===\n{{m|ga|is}} + {{m|ga|ea}} (literally, \"[[it]] [[is]]\")\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{IPA|ga|/ʃa/}}\n\n===Adverb===\n{{head|ga|adverb}}\n\n# [[yes]] {{q|to copula questions}}\n# [[right]], [[well]] {{q|topic introducer}}\n\n====Usage notes====\nThis is a contraction of an affirmative response to a question, and is found in response to  questions where the key verb is {{m|ga|is|id=copulasense}} or a present tense form thereof:\n: Q: An féidir leat cuidiú liom? — \"Can you help me?\" (literally, \"Possible for you to help me?\")\n: A: '''Sea'''. — \"Yes.\"\nInformally it may also be found as the answer to a question with a main verb, though this is considered incorrect. The standard response to such a question is to repeat the verb:\n: Q: Ar chuala tú mé? — \"Did you hear me?\"\n: A: Chuala. — \"Yes\" (literally, \"Heard\") ''or informally'' '''Sea'''.\n\n====Antonyms====\n* {{l|ga|ní hea}}\n* {{l|ga|nach ea}}\n\n==Middle English==\n\n===Noun===\n{{head|enm|noun|altform=1}}\n\n# {{tlb|enm|Early ME|or|Late ME}} {{alternative form of|enm|see|id=sea|t=sea}}\n\n==Mòcheno==\n\n===Etymology===\n{{root|mhn|ine-pro|*seykʷ-}}\nFrom {{inh|mhn|gmh|sē}}, from {{inh|mhn|goh|sēo}}, from {{inh|mhn|gmw-pro|*saiwi}}, from {{inh|mhn|gem-pro|*saiwiz||sea, ocean}}. Cognate with {{cog|de|See}}, {{cog|en|sea}}.\n\n===Noun===\n{{mhn-noun|m}}\n\n# [[lake]]\n\n===References===\n* {{R:CLM}}\n\n{{c|mhn|Landforms|Water}}\n\n==Old Irish==\n\n===Determiner===\n{{head|sga|determiner}}\n\n# {{alternative spelling of|sga|so}}\n\n==Old Swedish==\n\n===Alternative forms===\n* {{alter|gmq-osw|sīa}}\n\n===Etymology===\nFrom {{inh|gmq-osw|non|séa}} (West Norse {{m|non|sjá}}), from {{inh|gmq-osw|gem-pro|*sehwaną}}.\n\n===Verb===\n{{head|gmq-osw|verb|head=sēa}}\n\n# to [[see]]\n\n====Conjugation====\n{{gmq-osw-conj-st|sē|sā|sāgh|pressg=sēr|pres2pl=sēn|mppressg=sēs|subjpressg=sē|subjpres2pl=sēn|subjpres3pl=sēn|imp2pl=sēn|pastpcp=sēþer}}\n\n====Descendants====\n* {{desc|sv|se|sia}}\n\n==Plautdietsch==\n\n===Adverb===\n{{head|pdt|adverb}}\n\n# [[very]], [[intensely]]\n\n==Spanish==\n\n===Pronunciation===\n{{es-pr}}\n\n===Verb===\n{{head|es|verb form}}\n\n# {{es-verb form of|ser}}\n\n===See also===\n*{{l|es|así sea}}\n* {{l|es|aunque sea}}\n* {{l|es|maldita sea}}\n* {{l|es|o sea}}\n\n==Tongan==\n\n===Etymology===\n{{etymon|to|:bor|en:chair}}\nBorrowed from {{bor|to|en|chair}}.\n\n===Noun===\n{{head|to|noun}}\n\n# [[chair]]\n\n==Wolio==\n\n===Etymology===\nFrom {{inh|wlo|poz-pro|*səjəm}}.\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{IPA|wlo|/sea/}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{head|wlo|noun}}\n\n# [[ant]]\n\n===References===\n* {{cite-book|last=Anceaux|first=Johannes C.|year=1987|title=Wolio Dictionary (Wolio-English-Indonesian) / Kamus Bahasa Wolio (Wolio-Inggeris-Indonesia)|location=Dordrecht|publisher=Foris}}\n\n{{c|wlo|Insects}}"}}